def find_kth_sorted_string(test_cases):
    result = []
    for case in test_cases:
        (N, K, M, strings) = case
        indexed_strings = list(enumerate([s[:M] for s in strings]))
        indexed_strings.sort(key=lambda x: x[1])
        original_index = indexed_strings[K - 1][1]
        result.append(strings[original_index])
    return result
